apq8084: Fix thermal_zone for GPU

Comparing results on shamu/quark/kccat6 imply that the GPU's
thermal_zone is actually 10, not 11.  11 appears to be some arbitrary,
device-specific sensor, given the differeing readouts on different
devices.  For a discussion see

title: Add GPU sysfs entry for Zenfone 2 [ZE551ML/ZE550ML]
message:
Add GPU sysfs entry for Zenfone 2 [ZE551ML/ZE550ML]
had to fix up logical issues while dividing the frequency with 1000000, on dividing the frequency provided by zf2 i.e. in a range of 200000-640000, we get a zero (0), hence all the frequency in frequency table shows up as zero
I have moddified the code to check if the resultant value is less than 1, if so, we divide the freq by "1000", this gives us the exact frequency that a normal human should see.

Initially @BORETS24 made KA with GPU tab, but since he didn't release his source, I made the modifications.
if any of my changes breaks anything on any phone , please mail me

Signed-off-by: sayeed99 <sayeed.afridi2009@gmail.com>

title: Recovery: Add option for Soft Reboot
message:
Recovery: Add option for Soft Reboot

Option for soft reboot/hot reboot by killing zygote. All the services and apps registered to zygote gets killed and restarted. This effectively decreases reboot time when someone just wants to restart all the apps. The effect is mostly noticeable on older devices.

Busybox is required for pkill/killall commands.

Add support for override_vmin

Adds support for a simple 0/1 attribute at
/sys/devices/system/cpu/cpu0/cpufreq/override_vmin.  When enabled on
kernels that support it, this attribute forces CPU voltage to remain
above a safe limit.

This commit also bolts a setFullSpan method onto SwitchCompatCardItem to
allow the override_vmin card to display correctly in the CPU Voltage
fragment.

title: Fix window leak upon exiting MainActivity
message:
Fix window leak upon exiting MainActivity

AlertDialogs are tied to the current window, in this case MainActivity.
Once MainActivity is closed upon calling finish(), the AlertDialog is
not dismissed yet and thus causes a memory leak.

Fix this by dismissing the AlertDialog before closing MainActivity.

Signed-off-by: Zhao Wei Liew <zhaoweiliew@gmail.com>

Don't chip off the right edge of SwitchCompat
